it.essepuntato.earmark.core
Interface EARMARKNode

All Superinterfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable, EARMARKItem
All Known Subinterfaces:
EARMARKChildNode, EARMARKHierarchicalNode
All Known Implementing Classes:
Attribute, Comment, EARMARKDocument, Element, MarkupItem, PointerRange, Range, XPathPointerRange, XPathRange
public interface EARMARKNode
extends EARMARKItem

This interface defines all the methods that an EARMARK node have to implement. We call EARMARK node an EARMARK item that takes part in the graph structure of the document, i.e. all the markup items, the ranges and the document itself.

Author:
Silvio Peroni

Method Detail

cloneNode

EARMARKNode cloneNode(boolean deep)

This method clones the node.

The algorithm used for cloning may change depending on the particular type (EAMRARKNode.Type) of the calling node.

Parameters:
deep - if true, recursively clone the structure under the specified node; if false, clone only the node itself without recursion.
Returns:
the cloned node.

getUserData

java.lang.Object getUserData(java.lang.String key)
Retrieves the object associated to a key on a this node. The object must first have been set to this node by calling setUserData with the same key.

Parameters:
key - the key the object is associated to.
Returns:
the object associated to the given key on this node, or null if there was none.

setUserData

void setUserData(java.lang.String key,
                 java.lang.Object data)
Associate an object to a key on this node. The object can later be retrieved from this node by calling getUserData with the same key.

Parameters:
key - the key to associate the object to.
data - the object to associate to the given key, or null to remove any existing association to that key.
